<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/154596-so-i-ve-recently-had-to-urge-to-re-read">So, I&#39;ve recently had to urge to re-read this. Admittedly, it was partially due to me watching &quot;Troy&quot; when I was sick this past weekend, but I also feel like there were aspects of the story that I missed while speed reading it for school and over analyzing every spear throw.

Is there anyone who&#39;s felt this and actually followed through? Was it worth it? Is there anyone out there as crazy as I feel I am right now?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_154596'><a id="like_count_community_question_154596" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/154596?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">16 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1371.The_Iliad">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/154596-so-i-ve-recently-had-to-urge-to-re-read">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/154596-so-i-ve-recently-had-to-urge-to-re-read">See all 13 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/23212031-james-foster"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1465583160i/23212031._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/23212031-james-foster">James Foster</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I used to read it every year or two. After a pause of a few years, I am reading it again. Every time, it blows me away. I pick up new things. This tim<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I used to read it every year or two. After a pause of a few years, I am reading it again. Every time, it blows me away. I pick up new things. This time around, I realized how many people and gods were raging from the very beginning. Why wasn't this called the wrath of Agammemnon? Or Apollo? Or Chrysis? and so on. <br /><br />Is there a difference between rage and wrath?<br /><br />...well worth reading!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

